The paper discusses the design of complex activation functions for complex-valued neural networks, which falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The experiments involve complex-valued image classification, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the expressiveness of the proposed framework, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and signal processing (cs.SI).
